text: Carol A. Timmons ( - August 2, 2020) was an American military officer. She was the Adjutant General of the Delaware National Guard from February 1, 2017, until her retirement on March 2, 2019. She was awarded the Legion of Merit, Bronze Star Medal, and others. Timmons died on August 2, 2020 at the age of 62. ==References== Category:1958 births Category:2020 deaths Category:American generals Category:People from Wilmington, Delaware Category:Military people from Delaware
